# 🔱 LiTTree Lab Studios — CLINE RULES
# Read before executing ANY tool call or file modification.
# This file is consumed by the Cline VS Code extension.

[ENVIRONMENT]
- PLATFORM: Windows 11 (native, NOT WSL2).
- WORKSPACE_ROOT: C:\Users\litbi\CascadeProjects\litlab
- SHELL: cmd.exe (use Windows-style commands; do NOT invent Linux paths or tools).
- RUNTIME: Next.js 16 (Turbopack Engine) | React 19 | Tailwind v4 | pnpm 9.15+
- NODE: 22+

[PROJECT_TRUTH]
- This is a multi-agent AI app: LiTTree Lab Studios.
- Real subsystems: src/lib/jarvis.ts, src/lib/AgentOrchestrator.ts, src/lib/agent-logger.ts,
  src/lib/director-graph.ts, src/lib/supabase*.ts. Do not claim files exist that do not.
- Repository (git remote): https://github.com/LabsConnected/litlabs-website
- Branch: main
- Deployed on Vercel. Self-host via Dockerfile or docker-compose.yml.

[CRITICAL_RULES]
1. NEVER assume the workspace is empty or "minimal". If a file is missing, your context is
   wrong — read the file or run `dir` / `Get-ChildItem` first.
2. NEVER scaffold default Next.js / Tailwind / create-next-app boilerplate. The project is mature.
3. NEVER downgrade Next.js, React, or Turbopack.
4. NEVER introduce `~`, `$HOME`, `/mnt/c`, or any Linux path. The host is Windows.
5. NEVER edit `.env.local`, `.env*.local`, `.env.vercel-*`, or `.sb_anon_key`. They contain secrets
   and are git-ignored for a reason.
6. NEVER use `keytar` directly — it requires native compilation. It is a transitive dep only.
7. The Devin config is `.devin-config.json` (root-level). The legacy `devin.config.json` is
   kept for backward compatibility — if asked to update Devin, update BOTH files.

[COMMANDS]
- Dev server: `pnpm dev` (Turbopack on :3000) or `pnpm dev:webpack` as a fallback.
- Build: `pnpm build`
- Lint: `pnpm lint`
- Test: `pnpm test` (Vitest + jsdom)
- Type-check: `npx tsc --noEmit`
- Terminal server: `pnpm terminal:dev` (separate process on its own port).

[QUIRKS]
- `cleanDistDir: false` in next.config.ts to avoid Windows EPERM errors on `.next/` cleanup.
- `serverExternalPackages: ["jose"]` to fix the middleware NFT build error.
- Turbopack `root: __dirname` suppresses a lockfile-detection warning on Windows.
- `ignore-scripts=true` in `.npmrc` — postinstall scripts are skipped; install native deps manually.
- Supabase migrations live in `supabase/migrations/`; never write to `supabase/schema.sql`
  directly — it is regenerated by `supabase db pull`.
- Route groups: `(dashboard)`, `(auth)` are non-URL segments.

[DEPLOYMENT]
- Vercel: `git push origin main` triggers a production build via `.github/workflows/lighthouse.yml`.
- Docker: `docker build -t litlab .` (or use `docker/Dockerfile.terminal` for the terminal server).
- Heavy studio work (`/studio`, image generation) should run on GitHub Codespaces, not locally.
